# LDM College ERP - Forensic Audit & Recovery

## Objective
Transform a UI-heavy, disconnected ERP into a production-grade system.

## Tasks

- [/] **Phase 1: Forensic System Audit**
  - [ ] Gather database schema
  - [ ] Map backend API routes
  - [ ] Map frontend routes
  - [ ] Audit JWT/auth structure
  - [ ] Produce feature audit table
  - [ ] Create architecture diagram
  - [ ] Document broken assumptions

- [ ] **Phase 2: Canonical Data Model**
  - [ ] Define production-grade schema
  - [ ] Document relationships and keys
  - [ ] Produce executable SQL

- [ ] **Phase 3: RBAC Enforcement**
  - [ ] Create access control matrix
  - [ ] Define JWT payload structure
  - [ ] Define middleware logic

- [ ] **Phase 4: API ↔ UI Contract**
  - [ ] Document endpoint contracts
  - [ ] Identify missing APIs
  - [ ] Map UI components to APIs

- [ ] **Phase 5: Directory Structure**
  - [ ] Propose frontend structure
  - [ ] Propose backend structure

- [ ] **Phase 6: Recovery Execution Plan**
  - [ ] Create time-estimated checklist
  - [ ] Identify features to delete
  - [ ] Prioritize fixes
